The Christian right or the religious right The Christian right, also known as the religious right, is a term used to describe a political movement that aligns with conservative Christian values. This movement typically supports candidates and policies that align with their religious beliefs and moral standards. In the context of the United States, the religious right has been influential in shaping political discourse on issues such as abortion, same-sex marriage, and religious expression in public life.
