The political agenda of the Christian right The political agenda of the Christian right in the United States encompasses a diverse range of issues, primarily centered around conservative values and religious beliefs. This includes advocating for traditional family values, opposing abortion and embryonic stem cell research, supporting the rights of gun owners, and promoting the teaching of intelligent design or creationism in public schools. Additionally, the Christian right often supports capital punishment and law-and-order policies, while opposing euthanasia and same-sex marriage. These political positions are generally based on a interpretation of Christianity and are intended to promote what its proponents believe are moral and ethical standards in alignment with their religious teachings.
